question: tww..Those Who Wait?
answer: Fuck yes Those Who Wait! One of my best friends, @oddcoupler222, really outdid herself with this fic and I finally got off my ass and read it in the last few weeks. I loved it so much that I’m currently re-reading the whole thing along with the playlist Haley made for it, all the while peppering her with questions about headcanons and backstory and making requests for Sansa chapters from Margaery’s point of view. She indulges me every single time and I love her for that! It’s been a glorious time that I look forward to continuing with her. I can honestly say that no fic has made me immediately want to read it again or stayed in my brain so much that I feel the need to talk about it all the time. I’m just lucky that the author of it is someone I can literally scream at all the time about quotes I love and headcanons I’ve developed on my own, and she eats it all up instead of thinking I’m horribly annoying. I just want everyone to read it!

title: Sansa’s GOT S8 Armor Dress
body:
Sansa Stark will gear up for battle in the final season of Game of Thrones.

The Lady of Winterfell will get a costume change in season 8 to prepare for the arrival of the Army of the Dead.

“This is the first time I’ve had armor,” Sophie Turner tells EW.

The costume is not Jaime Lannister or Brienne of Tarth-style metal armor, but more like a jet-black ensemble made of thick leather or similar material.

“We the idea of it being very protective and she buttons herself up,” Turner says. “I wanted her to have a bit of armor and be a bit more warrior like. She’s like the warrior of Winterfell.”

ew.com

I was waiting to have high resolution pictures of Sansa’s Armor Dress before I post about it, but we are at four days left from the premiere and nothing…. 

So far this is what we have:

Bonus:

Fan Art by @Amanda__Howes

If Tywin found out about her real identity or if she was captured during the Red Wedding or if the Hound didn’t show up in time when she was running away, what do you think was gonna happen? For fucks sake, remember her face when she saw Robb’s body with Grey Wind’s head?

summary: I keep seeing posts analyzing Sansa’s armor dress in detail and that’s nice and all but I still maintain she looks like the...
body:
I keep seeing posts analyzing Sansa’s armor dress in detail and that’s nice and all but I still maintain she looks like the amazing front woman for a late ‘90s gothic-industrial band, fancy goth with an edge.  like she smokes, but only cloves, and is obsessed with Lord Byron and the Shelleys and scoffs at people who consider Nine Inch Nails real industrial music since Trent wholesale stole his breakthrough his from Skinny Puppy, obviously

the Night King and the army of the dead don’t stand a chance, she’ll look at them and puff her clove and roll her eyes and be like, “aren’t you a little bit obvious? Only way you zombies could be more of a cliche is if you wore fishnets on your arms and black lipstick.” and the Night King and his army would be devastated by her superior gothness and go find some park to do their zombie LARPing

summary: The whole Sansa vs Dany thing doesn’t have to do anything with a man. Sansa was beaten, abused and abandoned by her brother for...
question: The whole Sansa vs Dany thing doesn’t have to do anything with a man. Sansa was beaten, abused and abandoned by her brother for North’s independence. She suffered Ramsay to be back home. She had to accept Rickon’s death to get back winterfell. And now someone comes threatening to take this freedom away and you expect her to just roll over. She and Dany are one the opposite sides of the spectrum: Sansa’s cutting heads dialogue to Arya and Dany just burning everyone. Even Arya vs Dany make sense.
answer: Yeah on top of the problems with Northern independence, like you said Sansa and Dany’s style of ruling is completely different. D&D went out of their way to contrast the two for a reason. There’s very little Sansa and Dany can agree with  politically and I doubt they’d ever like each other no matter the situation unless D&D are invested in seeing a friendship and given their inability to have Sansa and Brienne be friends or even talk for longer than a minute, I very much doubt that will happen
